#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -euo pipefail

cat <<'EOF'
Tmux Help
=========

Session and windows
- Prefix c: new window in current directory
- Shift-Left / Shift-Right: previous / next window
- Click status-left: new window in current directory
- Click status-right: open choose-window

Panes
- Prefix s: split horizontally into top/bottom panes
- Prefix v: split vertically into left/right panes
- Prefix h/j/k/l: move to pane left/down/up/right
- Prefix Ctrl-h/j/k/l: resize pane left/down/up/right

Config
- Prefix r: reload ~/.tmux.conf
- Prefix ?: open this help popup

Status line
- Left side shows the tmux session name
- Right side shows SSH host when the active pane is SSH
- Otherwise right side shows hostname plus Git branch / repo / dirty state
- Window labels are inferred from the active pane process, such as nvim, yazi,
  git, docker, kubectl, Codex, or Claude

Managed helper scripts
- ~/.local/bin/tmux-pane-label
- ~/.local/bin/tmux-git-badge
- ~/.local/bin/tmux-ssh-host
EOF

if [[ -t 0 ]]; then
  printf '\nPress any key to close...'
  IFS= read -r -n 1 _
  printf '\n'
fi
